Uses of Class
com.objsys.asn1j.runtime.Asn1OctetString

    • Uses of Asn1OctetString in com.objsys.asn1j.runtime

      Subclasses of Asn1OctetString in com.objsys.asn1j.runtime 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  Asn1Base64BinaryString
      This is a container class for holding the components of an XML Base64Binary value.
      class  Asn1BCDString
      Asn1BCDString represents an OCTET STRING with an overridden toString method that converts the bytes to a character string of 0-9,A-E characters.
      class  Asn1ChoiceExt
      This is a container class for holding a CHOICE open type extension element.
      class  Asn1OpenType
      This is a container class for holding an ASN.1 open type value.
      class  Asn1TBCDString
      Asn1TBCDString represents an OCTET STRING with an overridden toString method that converts the bytes to a character string of [0-9*#abc] characters.
      class  Asn1XerOpenType
      Deprecated. 
      Use Asn1OpenType instead. You can use the constructors where you specify the encoding, and specify XER if you are populating with byte data that is a UTF-8 XML encoding of the actual value.
